              <title>The future of the VLE at the Open University? What would you like it to be?</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4652</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4652</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<blockquote dir="ltr">
<p>Where:&nbsp;<strong>The Hub, Medlar and Juniper Rooms, Walton Hall</strong></p>
<p>Time: <strong>12th&nbsp;October 2010, 10.00-12.00</strong></p>
<p>Presenters: <strong>Will Woods (IET), Barbara Poniatowska and Liz Burton-Pye (LIO)</strong></p>
<p>This event&nbsp;focused on the future visioning work and explained the developments planned within the current &ldquo;Roadmap Acceleration Programme&rdquo; as well as discussing requirements for the future VLE. Participants&nbsp;were asked to speak up on what they want (and really, really don't want) in the next generation OU VLE.&nbsp; They also&nbsp;heard more about the Roadmap Acceleration Programme and future learning systems.&nbsp;See also&nbsp;the <a href="http://podcast.open.ac.uk/oulife/podcast-626" target="_blank">Future of the VLE</a> podcast from David Wilson to learn more about what is being planned.</p>
<p>Participation took the form of a&nbsp;<a href="http://www.peopleandparticipation.net/display/Methods/World+Cafe" target="_blank">World Caf&eacute;</a>&nbsp;style session. This invited attendees to write on tablecloths at themed table&nbsp;to indicate their support for (or aversion to) particular aspects of key developments around &ldquo;User Generated Content&rdquo;, &ldquo;Personalisation&rdquo;, and &ldquo;Joining up&rdquo; (how we can mix the informal and formal learning environments, including how we join up our OER&rsquo;s with VLE and other repositories). Attendees'&nbsp;ideas and their how they see the various aspects of the OU's future learning system co-existing were&nbsp;a focus for the event.</p>
<p><strong>This event was recorded and is available to members of staff at the Open University via <a title="Stadium" href="http://stadium.open.ac.uk/webcast-ou/">Stadium</a></strong></p>
</blockquote>]]></description>
